President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 2015 as National Financial Capability Month in the United States. The purpose of this month is to raise awareness and promote financial literacy among Americans. The President emphasizes the importance of making informed financial decisions and understanding debt, as well as the need to provide resources and tools to help individuals improve their financial capabilities. The Obama administration has taken various actions to support financial education, such as launching campaigns, simplifying mortgage forms, and proposing new rules for financial advisors. The President encourages all Americans to increase their knowledge of personal finance and take advantage of the free financial resources available.